The paper presents a new algorithm for nonparametric Bayesian group factor analysis, which is a machine learning technique used in various fields including systems biology and neuroimaging. The paper focuses on the development of an efficient collapsed variational inference algorithm for this model, which is a common technique in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
